<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Stats</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: I am a level 62 magician wearing <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=33330">this equipment</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->. Since magelo doesnt yet credit stats over 255, my true int is 265, making my manapool for this test 4047.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Relevant AAxp</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: I have spell casting mastery 3, and spell casting fury 2. <br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mana regen</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: During this test i had a total of 20/tic standing mana regen (6 from xegonys, 13 from ft, and 1 from natural).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>How</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: For each spell, i ran 4 tests on the soulbinder in which i proceeded to chain nuke from full mana till effectively oom. I used jboots to bypass the recast delay for maximum dps. For the test without focus items i only ran 1 test, since there are comparitively little variations in performance (just resists, crits, and fizzles).<br>
<br>
This is how i estimated mana cost per cast:<br>
(a - (b(a * .01)) + ((c/6)d)) / e = mana per cast<br>
a = mana i started with (total mana pool size)<br>
b = mana i finished with (percent of the pool left)<br>
c = duration to empty mana pool<br>
d = total mana regen per tic<br>
e = # of times i could cast the spell till empty<br>
To get the average damage, i simply divided the total damage by the number of casts. <br>
To get the average ratio, i divided average damage by average mana cost. I then averaged these number across all 4 tests. These final numbers are how i measure the efficiency of both spells.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Results</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
1) <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Firebolt of Tallon</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, with focus items:<br>
Average dps: 332 <br>
Average mana cost per cast: 409<br>
Average damage per cast: 2168<br>
Average ratio: 5.3<br>
<br>
2) <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Firebolt of Tallon</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, without focus items:<br>
dps: 260 dps<br>
mana cost per cast: 443<br>
damage per cast: 1940<br>
ratio: 4.38<br>
<br>
3) <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">SoFB</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, with focus items:<br>
Average dps: 174 <br>
Average mana cost per cast: 242<br>
Average damage per cast: 1136<br>
Average ratio: 4.7<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Conclusions</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
Firebolt of tallon with focus items, when it can be used, is much more efficient than shock of firey blades even for a conjuration speced mage (5.3 ratio vs 4.7 ratio). Also, its dps is also nearly double that of sofb (332 vs 174). <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">However, sofb <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>is</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> more efficient for the conjuration speced mage than firebolt of tallon, without the new rare focus items</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> (4.7 vs 4.3<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Though unfocused FoT is faster than SoFB (260 vs 174), i dont think the increase in dps is enough to negate the lack of efficiency for the mage without focus items. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Attention wizzies: if you think its unfair, or overpowered that verant put this spell on a vendor, please note its only half the story. If this spell is to be more efficient than our existing spells, the mage needs to get <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>three</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> rare parchment turn ins.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Things to keep in mind</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
The numbers i quote are only accurate for a conjuration speced mage with scm 3 and fury 2. While the way the numbers <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>proportionally relate</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to each other shall remain mostly accurate for a mage with more or less aaxp, keep in mind the values themselves are far from static. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A> at: 11/10/02 8:31:36 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tainsumnr>Tain Sumnr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 271<br> <font color=#333333>(11/10/02 8:19:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: FoT vs SoFB, an in depth comparison (read this wizards)</span><hr size=1> It depends what your looking at.  Dps appears to be where power lies in pop, not efficiency like in previous expansions.  So a large increase in dps is enough to offset a lower efficiency, even though most likely you won't be seeing a lower efficiency anyways. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1374<br> <font color=#333333>(11/10/02 8:27:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=403.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.sebminas.com/eq/baby.gif WIDTH=60 HEI